Package de.oth.blocklib.world.fluids

Class ActiveFluidBlock

java.lang.Object
de.oth.blocklib.world.fluids.ActiveFluidBlock
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<ActiveFluidBlock>
public class ActiveFluidBlock
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<ActiveFluidBlock>
The ActiveFluidBlock represents a single block of an ActiveFluid. It is placed at a certain position and its fill level is defined by the containedAmount. This containedAmount can be higher than the specified MAX_CAPACITY. In this case the ActiveFluidBlock is under over-pressure and will be able to flow upwards. ActiveFluidBlocks need to be comparable to each other, to enable the possibility of sorting them after their containedAmount.
Author:
Tobias Mueller

      public void flowInto​(float amount)
      Adds a certain amount of fluid to the containedAmount of this ActiveFluidBlock. Prevents the ActiveFluidBlock from becoming passive, by resetting the becomePassiveCounter.
      Parameters:
